    {
      "id": "abd80ec8dac358a39ac15b57df365143535e8b07",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-21 16:08:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(4 comments)\n\nWe should never LASSERT as a method of error handling on information that is out of our control, like data received over the wire, from userspace, (or from disk, though that doesn't apply here).  We've moved beyond the stage where \"system crashes and we are notified to fix it\" is a workable model, unless the system can no longer function at all in that state. \n\nI'm not against LASSERT on internal state that we control, but definitely not on external state.  Note this is *not* a request to change this patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
